---
description: Voice AI and video support (OpenAI STT/TTS, video calls, transcription)
globs: backend/services/voice/**, backend/services/video/**, ai/voice/**, frontend/features/voice/**, frontend/features/video/**
---

Voice stack:
- OpenAI API for speech-to-text (STT) and text-to-speech (TTS) for voice bot and real-time assistance.
- Call recording and storage (e.g. S3) with metadata in Supabase.
- Voice tone analysis and real-time call assistance as per PRD; use OpenAI or dedicated models via API.

Video stack:
- Real-time video support between customers and agents (WebRTC or managed service); screen sharing, file sharing, in-call chat.
- AI transcript generation from video/audio and call summary generation (e.g. post-call) using OpenAI or batch jobs.

Rules:
- Keep voice pipeline separate from text chat pipeline; share conversation/ticket context where needed.
- Transcriptions and summaries must be stored and linked to the conversation/call record for history and analytics.
- Do not stream raw audio to prompts; use STT first, then text-based RAG/agents; TTS for responses when voice output is required.
- Prefer async or worker-based processing for recording uploads and summary generation to avoid blocking request paths.
- Secure storage and access control for recordings and PII; comply with retention and consent (GDPR, etc.).

Do not:
- Hardcode OpenAI API keys; use config/env.
- Store unencrypted voice/video recordings in publicly accessible locations.
- Mix voice-specific business logic with generic chat in the same untyped flow; use clear boundaries.
